;;; ============================================================
;;; 05-macros
;;; syntax-rules, hygiene, macro expansion
;;; ============================================================
;;;
;;; Regression tripwires for the macro expander.  Each entry is pinned to a specific
;;; bug that was fixed -- this is NOT feature coverage.  Only Scheme-
;;; observable, non-spec regressions belong here; spec deviations go in
;;; R7RS-Compliance-Tests/, internal-only bugs in undercarriage gc_test.cpp.
;;; See 00-conventions.md for the full routing rule.
;;;
;;; HOW TO ADD A REGRESSION
;;;   - Append to the END of this file.  Tests run top-to-bottom; keep them
;;;     in chronological order (oldest bug first) so the file reads as a
;;;     timeline for this subsystem.
;;;   - Precede each case with a provenance comment so it stays meaningful:
;;;        ; REG <yyyy-mm-dd> -- <commit-or-issue> -- <one line: what broke>
;;;        ; Symptom: <what the user saw before the fix>
;;;   - Keep the reproducer MINIMAL, then give the expected result:
;;;        >>> (expression)
;;;        ==> expected             ; or:  %%% %any-error%
;;;
; REG 2026-06-17 -- cpp d4b5893 / py 5779403 -- ellipsis match-count mismatch
; Symptom: two same-depth ellipsis pattern variables matched an unequal number
;   of times, combined in one template, were indexed out of bounds -- cppScheme2
;   fabricated #<unknown> and SEGFAULTED when the later var was empty; pyScheme
;   leaked a host IndexError.  Fixed to a clean syntax error (R7RS 4.3.2: unequal
;   ellipsis counts is "an error").  The same length check also prevents the
;   empty-var segfault, so this graceful case guards both.
>>> (let () (define-syntax zp (syntax-rules () ((_ (a ...) (b ...)) (list (list a b) ...)))) (zp (1 2 3) (10 20)))
%%% %any-error%
